#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/Threshold.rst:4
#: 74cff8c2eca040b9af64341475c6aeb0
msgid ""
"The Threshold model describes a diffusion process in which each node in a"
" network adopts a behavior (becomes active) when a sufficient fraction or"
" weighted sum of its neighbors are already active. Unlike the Independent"
" Cascades model, which uses independent stochastic activations, the "
"Threshold model relies on **deterministic or probabilistic thresholds** "
"that control adoption."
msgstr ""

